meanings.definition: To surpass in performance or achievement.
meanings.sent1: The new model outperforms the old one.
meanings.sent2: She always outperforms her classmates in math.
meanings.sent3: The tortoise outperforms the hare in this race!
meanings.sent5: The sun outperforms the moon in brightness.

meanings.definition: To do better than someone or something else in a particular activity or competition.
meanings.sent1: The athlete outperforms his opponents in every match.
meanings.sent2: Our team consistently outperforms the competition.
meanings.sent3: The squirrel outperforms the birds in gathering nuts.
meanings.sent4: Her determination outperforms any obstacles in her way.
meanings.sent5: The wind outperforms the stillness in moving leaves.
